{
  "title": "Principle 9 -  Decisions should be informed by indicators.",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "62dd989f4a93de5f",
      "text": "Monitor the impact of scaling using a set of indicators based on a mix of quantitative (e.g., throughput) and qualitative (e.g., team morale) metrics. "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "b183966ee949ed5f",
      "text": "Without them, assessing the true impact of the decisions taken, and act accordingly, would be very difficult, if not impossible. Indicators should be:\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "af07a871ec88cc27",
      "text": "- Based on metrics that look at the system from different perspectives to provide a balanced view. For example, measuring (and optimizing) only flow metrics (throughput, lead time, cycle time, etc.) doesn’t show the bad effect on code quality and defect rate that decisions like pushing the teams to do overtime in order to improve throughput, have;\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "dcba6171ab78bc38",
      "text": "- Used to track progress and adapt accordingly, not to set targets or assess the performance of individuals, as they will cause the metrics to be gamed, making them useless;\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "f37afcd9862315a3",
      "text": "- Analysed in context—e.g., an explicit decision to push to a deadline to onboard a big customer, will probably show as a drop in code quality in some of the metrics; however, it may have been the correct business decision to take. Of course, there has to be an action to repay the accrued technical debt.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "2860bbe5f5648856",
      "text": "Track, as you try to scale, the variation of the delivery throughput and lead time, the responsiveness and resilience to sudden unexpected events (consider also monitoring other components of agility, described by [[David S. Alberts and Richard E. Hayes, 2003]]), as well as the satisfaction of customers and of those doing the work."
    },
    {
      "type": "pagefold",
      "id": "62ed476e4d365b8d",
      "text": "Discussions"
